data.abstract:
CO2 transport is an integral part in the whole CCS (carbon capture and storage) chain. One of the most important factors affecting this part is the quality of CO2 that is being transported. This is a challenging issue because impurities in CO2 vary greatly in quantity and in quality depending on the sources of CO2. Moreover, the requirement for impurity limits also varies depending on the destination of the CO2. Currently, there is no existing regulation for CO2 standard for transport. Yet, this issue could have significant impacts on CO2 capture and transportation. This article reviews the operating experiences of the current existing CO2 pipelines, outlines CO2 quality guidelines from different institutions, analyzes various CO2 capture technologies and related impurities, explores impurities impacts on pipeline transportation, and outlines the issues facing the CO2 transport that need to be solved. 


Keywords: 

CO2 capture; 
CO2 transportation; 
CO2 quality and standards; 
pipeline; 
greenhouse gas
